The paper deals with transfer learning, clustering, and similarity functions, which are all topics commonly studied in the machine learning community. The use of similarity networks and clustering networks suggests a focus on deep learning techniques, which are often studied in the cs.LG sub-category. The use of image datasets such as Omniglot, ImageNet, and Office-31 also suggests a focus on computer vision, which is commonly studied in the cs.CV sub-category. The paper also deals with unsupervised learning and domain adaptation, which are topics commonly studied in the cs.AI and cs.CL sub-categories. Finally, the use of robust clustering algorithms suggests a focus on optimization and algorithms, which are commonly studied in the cs.NE sub-category.
